@{
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

@section PageSpecificStyles {
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/community.css">
}



<div class="main-thread">
    <div class="new-post">
        <div class="profile-pic">
            <img src="/imgs/lego.png" alt="profile picture"/>
        </div>
        <div class="post-body">
            <input type="text" placeholder="Post a message..."/>
        </div>
        <div class="post-btn">
            <button>Post</button>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="thread-card">
        <div class="main-info">
            <div class="profile-pic">
                <img src="/imgs/lego.png" alt="profile picture"/>
            </div>
            <div class="profile-and-post">
                <div class="top-row">
                    <h3>BrickBuilder101</h3>
                    <p>3m</p>
                </div>
                <h5>Hello from a New Enthusiast!</h5>
                <p>Hi everyone! I'm new here but have been building with LEGO since I was a kid. I just finished my latest project, the LEGO Creator Expert Roller Coaster, and it was a blast! I’m looking forward to sharing tips with all of you and getting some inspiration for my next big build. What was the first complex set you ever built?</p>
            <img src="/imgs/rollercoaster.png" height="300px"/>
                </div>
        </div>
        <div class="symbols">
            <a><i class="fa-solid fa-heart"></i></a>  
            <a><i class="fa-solid fa-comment"></i></a>
            <a><i class="fa-solid fa-share"></i></a>
            <a><i class="fa-solid fa-paper-plane"></i></a> 
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="thread-card">
        <div class="main-info">
            <div class="profile-pic">
                <img src="/imgs/lego.png" alt="profile picture"/>
            </div>
            <div class="profile-and-post">
                <div class="top-row">
                    <h3>MasterArchitect</h3>
                    <p>5h</p>
                </div>
                <h5>Monthly Challenge: Architectural Wonders</h5>
                <p>This month, I’m challenging everyone to create their favorite architectural wonder using LEGO. It could be anything from the Eiffel Tower to your own dream skyscraper. I’ve started with a mini-model of the Sydney Opera House and can’t wait to see what you come up with. Let's share progress photos and support each other’s creativity!</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="symbols">
            <a><i class="fa-solid fa-heart"></i></a>  
            <a><i class="fa-solid fa-comment"></i></a>
            <a><i class="fa-solid fa-share"></i></a>
            <a><i class="fa-solid fa-paper-plane"></i></a> 
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="thread-card">
        <div class="main-info">
            <div class="profile-pic">
                <img src="/imgs/lego.png" alt="profile picture"/>
            </div>
            <div class="profile-and-post">
                <div class="top-row">
                    <h3>PieceByPiece</h3>
                    <p>6h</p>
                </div>
                <h5>Best Techniques for a Sturdy Build</h5>
                <p>Hey everyone, I wanted to share some techniques I’ve learned over the years for making structures more stable, especially for tall buildings. <a>I’ve found that interlocking bricks diagonally can really help</a>. Does anyone else have other tips or tricks they use for building stable and intricate designs?</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="symbols">
            <a><i class="fa-solid fa-heart"></i></a>  
